HEADWORD: chivaree
<hw>chivaree</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a noisy mock serenade (made by
banging pans and kettles) to a newly married couple.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> shivaree, charivari, callithump,
callathump.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

